Sentencas: Low temperature solid oxide fuel cell (LTSOFC, 300-600 degrees C) is developed with advantages compared to conventional SOFC (800-1000 degrees C).
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Performances of LiNiCuZn Oxides as Anode and Cathode Catalyst for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The electrodes with good catalytic activity, high electronic and ionic conductivity are required to achieve high power output.
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Performances of LiNiCuZn Oxides as Anode and Cathode Catalyst for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: In this work, a LiNiCuZn oxides as anode and cathode catalyst is prepared by slurry method.
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Performances of LiNiCuZn Oxides as Anode and Cathode Catalyst for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The structure and morphology of the prepared LiNiCuZn oxides are characterized by X-ray diffraction and field emission scanning electron microscopy.
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Performances of LiNiCuZn Oxides as Anode and Cathode Catalyst for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The LiNiCuZn oxides prepared by slurry method are nano Li0.28Ni0.72O, ZnO and CuO compound.
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Performances of LiNiCuZn Oxides as Anode and Cathode Catalyst for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The nano-crystallites are congregated to form ball-shape particles with diameter of 800-1000 nm.
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Performances of LiNiCuZn Oxides as Anode and Cathode Catalyst for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The LiNiCuZn oxides electrodes exhibits high ion conductivity and low polarization resistance to hydrogen oxidation reaction and oxygen reduction reaction at low temperature.
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Performances of LiNiCuZn Oxides as Anode and Cathode Catalyst for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The LTSOFC using the LiNiCuZn oxides electrodes demonstrates good cell performance of 1000 mW cm(-2) when it operates at 470 degrees C.
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Performances of LiNiCuZn Oxides as Anode and Cathode Catalyst for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: It is considered that nano-composite would be an effective way to develop catalyst for LTSOFC.
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Performances of LiNiCuZn Oxides as Anode and Cathode Catalyst for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell
